y exist and are being applied to crucial issues around human-caused climate change, feeding the world’s growing population, and exploiting natural resources. Deeply informed yet accessibly written, Dodging Extinction is nothing short of a guidebook for saving the planet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aConservation of natural resources. 0aExtinction (Biology). 0aMass extinctions. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh  aavoiding extinction.  abiology.  aclimate change.  aearth.  aevolutionary history.  afood production.  afuture of the planet.  ageologic history.  aglobal catastrophe.  aglobal economy.  aglobal ecosystem.  aglobal warming.  ahuman caused.  ahumanity.  amass extinction.  anatural resources.  apaleobiologist.  apaleobiology.  apaleontologist.  apolitical commentary.  asaving the planet.  ascience.  asixth mass extinction.  asustainable agriculture.  asustainable living.  atechnology.  atheoretical.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015z97831106211120 cprintz978052027437240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095909540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520959095423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520959095/original  a978-3-11-062111-2  University of California Press Complete Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY